  "title": "Understanding the Importance of Body Temperature",
  "lessonText": "Body temperature regulation is crucial for maintaining overall health.",
  "data": {
    "content": "- Body temperature reflects the body's ability to generate and dissipate heat.\n- Normal range is typically between 97°F (36.1°C) and 99°F (37.2°C).\n- It plays a vital role in metabolic processes.\n- Fever can indicate infection or illness.\n- Cold sensations may signal low body temperature or poor circulation."
  }
}
